//CEASAR CIPHEER C CODE//

    #include <stdio.h>
    #include <ctype.h>
    
    int main() {
        char text[100];
        int shift;
    
        printf("Enter text: ");
        fgets(text, sizeof(text), stdin);
    
        printf("Enter shift value: ");
        scanf("%d", &shift);
    
        for (int i = 0; text[i] != '\0'; i++) {
            char ch = text[i];
    
            if (isalpha(ch)) {
                char base = isupper(ch) ? 'A' : 'a';
                ch = (ch - base + shift) % 26 + base;
            }
    
            text[i] = ch;
        }
    
        printf("Encrypted text: %s", text);
    
        return 0;
    }

    Through this write-up on cryptography, I learned that cryptography is not only about hiding messages but also about protecting data confidentiality, integrity, and authentication in cybersecurity systems. 
I also realized the importance of encryption, decryption, and hashing in securing passwords, online transactions, and private communication. Studying basic cryptographic techniques helped me understand how 
modern security systems are built and why weak or outdated encryption methods are no longer safe to use.


